<function>

access:   public

name: scope

param: mixed, $value

param: int, $size

param: int, $scope

param: bool, $blank, false

return: bool

</function>

See a value has only a certain number of digits and decimals.

* Parameters:

 * mixed //$value//: The value to validate.

 * int //$size//: The total number of digits allowed in the value, excluding the negative sign and decimal point.

 * int //$scope//: The maximum number of decimal places.

 * bool //$blank//: Allow blank values to be valid.

* Returns bool: True if valid, false if not.

The value must be numeric, can be no longer than the \\$size\\,
and can have no more decimal places than the \\$scope\\.